<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-09-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-09-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="255" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d255">
                        <head>255. Telegram 809 to Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d255fn1">Source: Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/9–3055. Official
                                Use Only. Repeated to Prague for the Ambassador as telegram 89.
                                Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_MWP_1">McConaughy</persName>;
                                cleared by Furnas (R) and Yager (DRF) in draft and by Capella
                                (FE/EX) and Sebald.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-09-30">September 30, 1955, 6:50
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <pb facs="d255-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d255-1"/>
                        <p>809. For <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>.</p>
                        <p><persName corresp="#p_CPW_1">Peter Colm</persName> of DRF being detailed
                            Geneva assist <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>. Arrive
                            about October 11. <persName corresp="#p_CRN_1">Clough</persName> should
                            return Department as soon as practicable.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_DJF_1"><hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi></persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>